# TypeORM (MySQL) rules

Database is **MySQL** (`mysql2`), `type: 'mysql'`. There is no postgres anywhere.

## Entities

- Extend `BaseEntity` (mutable, soft-deletable, user-attributed) or
  `SystemBaseEntity` (system rows, no user attribution) from `@core/database`.
- Every entity sets `protected static uidPrefix = '<prefix>'`; `uid` is generated
  on insert as `<prefix>_<nanoid>` (32-char varchar, unique, indexed).
- `id` is an auto-increment bigint PK; `uid` is the external/business identifier.
- Text columns use `utf8mb4` (matches `docker/mysql/init.sql`).
- Repositories are injected and used **only** inside a lib's `services/` — never
  in an app, never in a controller.

## Migrations only — never synchronize

- `synchronize: false` always (including tests).
- All schema changes are TypeORM migrations under `/database/migrations`:
  - `npm run migration:generate -- database/migrations/<Name>` to diff,
  - `npm run migration:run` / `npm run migration:revert` to apply/rollback.
- Migration class names are PascalChange + timestamp; keep `up`/`down` symmetric.
- Never edit an applied migration — add a new one.
- Seed data is not a migration; use `npm run seed` (`database/seeds`).

The CLI data source is `database/data-source.ts` (globs entities from
`libs/**/*.entity.ts` + `apps/**/*.entity.ts`, migrations from
`database/migrations/*.ts`, `migrationsTableName: 'migrations'`).
